Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.81,0:00:04.64,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, their donuts are made with soy pulp,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.64,0:00:06.98,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,so they're low sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.40,0:00:10.70,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but they look amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.70,0:00:13.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But aren't they fried in oil?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.35,0:00:14.74,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Won't it make us fat?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.97,0:00:17.97,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They've got holes in the \Nmiddle. We'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.97,0:00:20.75,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They said they're low calorie \Nsince they're low sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.13,0:00:24.25,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Eat too much of anything, \Nand you'll still get fat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.90,0:00:27.25,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,We've arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.64,0:00:30.88,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Pretty tasteful, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.08,0:00:35.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Find the question that solves the mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.84,0:00:37.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apply miraculous detective skills \Nto the secrets of the heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.97,0:00:39.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A fashionable café known for its donuts!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.79,0:00:42.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What shocking truth will the \Nhigh school detective reveal?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.40,0:00:43.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.73,0:00:45.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.75,0:00:48.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.00,0:02:34.00,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(398,1)}Murder at the Townhouse Café
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.73,0:02:31.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Murder at the Townhouse Café!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.41,0:02:37.63,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.95,0:02:39.65,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What a pretty yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.82,0:02:42.89,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.18,0:02:44.43,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.43,0:02:45.90,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.90,0:02:50.77,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,A place like this is sure to look amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.13,0:02:53.07,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.56,0:03:00.03,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Our staff member Sakai takes \Ngreat care of our yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.69,0:03:00.11,Tomita,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(236,348)}Tomita Satoshi (37)\NManager
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.03,0:03:03.07,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,It's truly impressive. I'm proud of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.50,0:03:06.60,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it really is wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.60,0:03:08.14,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.14,0:03:09.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.44,0:03:11.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, do you work here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.76,0:03:13.53,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, my apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.53,0:03:16.64,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Tomita, the manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.64,0:03:19.67,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you to your seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.67,0:03:21.02,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,This way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.20,0:03:24.97,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What should we get?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.18,0:03:27.73,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't we come here to eat donuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.73,0:03:30.64,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we'll eat donuts as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.49,0:03:32.66,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,What can I get you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.56,0:03:38.08,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you recommend?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.08,0:03:42.15,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,Our soy pulp donuts are our number one item.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.60,0:03:48.16,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,They're low sugar and made to order, \Nso you can enjoy them fresh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.25,0:03:56.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But judging by the state of things, this \Nplace's popularity suddenly spiked and waned.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.15,0:03:57.80,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.36,0:04:00.74,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I brought the soy pulp \Nout of the storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.51,0:04:02.93,Sakai,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(229,397)}Sakai Chitose (19)\NPart-time Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.74,0:04:02.53,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.07,0:04:07.72,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,All right. I've decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.72,0:04:10.86,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like a hot Darjeeling tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.86,0:04:15.11,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Also, one shibazuke and cream \Ndonut, two matcha and mayo donuts,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.11,0:04:20.43,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,two chocolate dream donuts, one plain \Ndonut, and one molasses crepe parfait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.43,0:04:21.46,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,How about you, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.68,0:04:24.32,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.50,0:04:26.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? The same thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.56,0:04:29.38,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, you'll have orange juice, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.38,0:04:30.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.61,0:04:33.11,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.11,0:04:35.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, they're beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.38,0:04:36.89,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They look delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.89,0:04:39.26,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.26,0:04:43.92,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but we may have ordered too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.08,0:04:47.89,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's dig in!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.41,0:04:50.52,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,Sakai, I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.52,0:04:51.18,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.63,0:04:52.81,DCMain,TOMITA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.81,0:04:54.23,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.23,0:04:55.45,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.50,0:04:57.83,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.83,0:05:01.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No. I'm not sure which to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.69,0:05:04.17,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.17,0:05:06.61,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I had a bite, but it's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.61,0:05:10.95,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that the donut you just ate?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.17,0:05:14.05,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Say, "Ah."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.56,0:05:18.96,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,An indirect kiss...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.35,0:05:21.59,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right? Good, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.04,0:05:23.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.96,0:05:32.30,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,These are lighter than \Nexpected, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.30,0:05:34.60,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I could eat these forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.61,0:05:42.02,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,There's sourness and saltiness \Nbehind the sweetness, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.02,0:05:42.69,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.07,0:05:54.12,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The sound of frying donuts really \Nwhets the appetite, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.12,0:05:55.35,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.18,0:05:57.53,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.53,0:06:00.63,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, doesn't he seem kind of suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.73,0:06:04.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.93,0:06:08.08,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,He keeps looking around \Neverywhere. He seems restless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.56,0:06:11.97,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,And doesn't that customer seem odd, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.82,0:06:17.73,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's more like he's observing \Ndonuts, not eating them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.27,0:06:22.10,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't a single decent \Ncustomer in this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.66,0:06:26.69,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What was that beeping sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.69,0:06:28.74,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I heard it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.71,0:06:34.87,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take your empty plates.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:39.25,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm stuffed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.46,0:06:41.15,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I can't eat anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.15,0:06:43.01,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You ate too much, Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.01,0:06:45.75,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of eating too much, \Nit looks like he did, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.00,0:06:48.41,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He's having a pretty rough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.41,0:06:50.77,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if he'll make it to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.82,0:06:58.58,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, those were pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.58,0:07:02.39,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They seemed pretty high-level \Nfor low sugar donuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.39,0:07:04.18,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But they're still fried.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.18,0:07:06.61,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Should we have eaten that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.61,0:07:10.30,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be fine. That's why \Nthey're low sugar, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.37,0:07:12.16,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.63,0:07:15.53,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.92,0:07:20.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.98,0:07:22.75,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.20,0:07:24.37,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,The manager...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.95,0:07:27.23,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.42,0:07:29.13,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.42,0:07:31.68,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Kid, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.68,0:07:34.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The manager collapsed in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.13,0:07:35.18,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.57,0:07:36.93,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was he struck?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.79,0:07:40.56,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The weapon was probably that mop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.58,0:07:45.56,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit used those gloves on the ground \Nto avoiding leaving fingerprints behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.59,0:07:47.87,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Or could it be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.87,0:07:51.17,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, let's call an \Nambulance and the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.17,0:07:52.07,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.79,0:07:59.20,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,The victim is Tomita Satoshi-san, \Nthe owner of this café.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.76,0:08:04.73,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,He was struck on the back of the head with \Na blunt object while in the café's bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.41,0:08:09.91,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, these people \Nwere inside the café.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.91,0:08:11.46,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You girls again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.46,0:08:12.84,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.21,0:08:16.60,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Could you tell us your names?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.49,0:08:18.35,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.35,0:08:21.50,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Sakai Chitose. I'm a student.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.50,0:08:24.23,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, I work here part-time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.77,0:08:28.19,Furukawa,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(234,392)}Furukawa Yoshihisa (34)\NCustomer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.82,0:08:27.37,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}My name is Furukawa Yoshihisa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.37,0:08:30.60,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I happened to be having tea here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.60,0:08:33.86,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing suspicious about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.15,0:08:37.57,Nonaka,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(238,387)\3c&H8F6C6A&}Nonaka Kenji (42)\NCafé Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.22,0:08:36.30,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}My name is Nonaka Kenji.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.30,0:08:39.35,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I operate a café in this neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.35,0:08:42.34,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.13,0:08:47.56,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,you always come to scout out our café \Nand steal our recipes, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.56,0:08:49.91,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.91,0:08:54.22,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,My recipes are the product \Nof my own creativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.22,0:08:56.28,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No one cares about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.28,0:09:01.39,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You gathered us here because you think \None of us is the culprit, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.66,0:09:03.52,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't said that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.52,0:09:06.89,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We just thought we'd ask you some questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.89,0:09:11.09,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,For someone to attack the \Nmanager in the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.09,0:09:15.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,they would've had to pass through this café \Nwhere you could have seen them, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.54,0:09:16.91,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.41,0:09:21.32,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,The only person who left this room while \Nthe manager was in the bathroom was...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.92,0:09:23.44,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Nonaka-san, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.92,0:09:26.12,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.12,0:09:27.46,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.77,0:09:31.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But you're the only one who left his seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.26,0:09:34.84,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I just happened to go the bathroom then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.84,0:09:39.39,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, Furukawa is \Nway more suspicious than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.39,0:09:42.45,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,He seemed nervous and had been behaving \Noddly since he entered the café.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.72,0:09:47.11,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm not nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.11,0:09:49.87,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now. Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.87,0:09:52.14,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us one at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.44,0:09:56.03,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What you did after the manager \Nwent to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.48,0:09:59.77,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I was frying donuts in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.23,0:10:03.29,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I never visited the tables during that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.68,0:10:08.29,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, we \Nheard the donuts frying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.59,0:10:12.99,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I was at my table the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.50,0:10:16.80,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone here should've seen me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.27,0:10:19.24,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.24,0:10:22.82,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.82,0:10:24.81,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Nonaka-san, how about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.20,0:10:26.30,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.11,0:10:29.48,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I certainly went to the bathroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.13,0:10:34.32,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,but by the time I entered, the \Nmanager was already on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.56,0:10:39.12,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you're the \Nonly one who left his seat
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.12,0:10:42.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,to go to the bathroom when \Nthe crime took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.60,0:10:45.87,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,So, what? That doesn't mean I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.06,0:10:49.75,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But aren't you the manager of a rival café?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.96,0:10:51.03,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.03,0:10:52.67,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,This place sells donuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.67,0:10:54.39,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I sell waffles.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.39,0:10:56.38,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,They're totally different genres of food.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.70,0:10:58.55,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.55,0:11:00.45,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I guess they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.45,0:11:01.52,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.09,0:11:03.02,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.76,0:11:06.06,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.06,0:11:10.81,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but we'd like \Nyou to wait elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.41,0:11:12.81,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We appreciate your understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.18,0:11:15.32,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Based on the circumstances \Nand testimony so far,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.00,0:11:18.74,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Nonaka-san seems suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.38,0:11:23.35,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But should we trust that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.12,0:11:31.45,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure, we finished \Nquestioning the suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.45,0:11:39.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,First, sales have declined at the \Ncafé Nonaka-san operates recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.08,0:11:45.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, he's not sure if his café \Nwill survive beyond a few more months.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.97,0:11:42.88,Hallway,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,721)}Tables
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.97,0:11:46.97,LR Names,BLUE,0000,0000,0000,,Nonaka
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.43,0:11:44.01,Hallway,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Hallway
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.14,0:11:46.97,Men's Bathroom,BOTTOM LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Men's \NBathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.22,0:11:46.97,Entrance,BOTTOM CENTER,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Entrance
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.30,0:11:46.97,Woman's Bathroom,TOP LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Women's \NBathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.30,0:11:46.97,Small Hallway,TOP CENTER,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Hallway
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.35,0:11:46.97,Yard,RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Yard
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.69,0:11:55.76,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Next, Furukawa-san said he had money \Nproblems with the manager Tomita-san in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.98,0:11:58.98,LR Names,BLUE,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(529,45)}Furukawa
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.60,0:11:55.40,Hallway,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Tables
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.81,0:11:56.23,Hallway,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Hallway
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.75,0:11:58.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}They both seem \Nto have motives.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.19,0:11:58.98,Men's Bathroom,BOTTOM LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Men's\NBathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.27,0:11:58.98,Woman's Bathroom,TOP LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Women's\NBathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.27,0:11:58.98,Small Hallway,TOP CENTER,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Hallway
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.36,0:11:58.98,Yard,RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Yard
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.40,0:11:58.98,Entrance,BOTTOM CENTER,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Entrance
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.98,0:12:04.49,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, the part-time employee Sakai-san \Ndidn't get along with the manager very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.08,0:12:07.35,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,According to part-time employee Sakai-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.92,0:12:12.29,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,the gloves left at the crime \Nscene belong to Nonaka-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.29,0:12:13.25,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.25,0:12:14.50,Kitchen,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(1,100)}Kitchen
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.25,0:12:20.26,LR Names,BLUE,0000,0000,0000,,Sakai
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.72,0:12:16.07,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Nonaka-san is a regular here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.07,0:12:20.26,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,He clearly recognized those gloves \Nbecause he always wears them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.17,0:12:16.54,Hallway,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Yard
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.69,0:12:25.54,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The gloves of the only man without \Nan alibi were at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.54,0:12:27.15,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Does that settle it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.15,0:12:31.52,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,As long as Nonaka-san doesn't come \Nup with an alibi, it must be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.40,0:12:33.70,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.25,0:12:35.86,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.04,0:12:43.45,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Nonaka-san, allow me to be direct.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.73,0:12:46.16,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,These gloves are yours, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.09,0:12:48.41,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.66,0:12:53.91,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-They're certainly mine,\Nbut I lost them a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.13,0:12:56.43,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So they're yours, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.43,0:13:00.34,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have an alibi, you do have a \Nmotive, and then there's this material evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.63,0:13:03.41,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any explanation for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.41,0:13:04.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.46,0:13:05.18,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.14,0:13:07.34,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.34,0:13:08.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.59,0:13:12.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Nonaka-san, could you \Naccompany us to the station?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.33,0:13:15.32,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,B-But... you have to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.32,0:13:16.56,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I really didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.75,0:13:18.61,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell us about it at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.61,0:13:20.32,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Please come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.65,0:13:23.47,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't have anything to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.43,0:13:28.65,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.89,0:13:35.37,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.45,0:13:40.50,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure, could you \Nwait to escort him away?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.93,0:13:41.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.95,0:13:44.76,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you figure out who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.19,0:13:46.69,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,At first glance,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.69,0:13:52.76,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,all the evidence in this case seems to \Nindicate that Nonaka-san is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.08,0:13:58.37,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, if Nonaka-san \Nreally did do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.37,0:14:00.87,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,don't you think it was a bit too sloppy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.87,0:14:02.13,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.13,0:14:05.78,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,If it were me, I wouldn't \Nhave left the gloves behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.06,0:14:07.68,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,And Furukawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.22,0:14:12.20,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Like us, you didn't go near the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.20,0:14:15.91,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Considering that, your alibi seems perfect,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.09,0:14:17.99,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,but is it really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.99,0:14:20.50,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a perfect alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.50,0:14:22.79,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You could at least let me go early.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.13,0:14:26.47,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,And finally, the part-timer Sakai-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.12,0:14:30.10,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You said you were in the \Nkitchen the whole time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.10,0:14:32.30,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,but we didn't see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.53,0:14:35.64,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I was frying donuts in the \Nkitchen the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.64,0:14:37.89,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, the fact that you didn't see me
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.89,0:14:40.81,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,proves I was in the kitchen the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.31,0:14:45.87,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Considering their testimony,\Nit sounds like the culprit is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.37,0:14:50.07,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What? You still think I did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.07,0:14:51.24,Hallway,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Tables
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.07,0:14:51.65,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.65,0:14:56.10,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You headed towards the men's \Nbathroom and attacked Tomita-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.82,0:14:52.37,Hallway,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Hallway
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.10,0:14:58.65,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,who was already in the \Nbathroom, with a nearby mop.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.99,0:15:03.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a very natural and \Nplausible series of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.31,0:15:07.16,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Next, let's recreate Furukawa-san's actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.16,0:15:08.80,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ran, could you show us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.66,0:15:10.44,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.56,0:15:16.68,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see. Furukawa-san was \Nin his seat the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.84,0:15:19.67,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,For him to attack Tomita-san \Nin the bathroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.56,0:15:18.35,Hallway,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Tables
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.81,0:15:19.31,Hallway,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Hallway
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.37,0:15:25.69,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't have been possible for \Nhim to do it without us noticing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.04,0:15:29.19,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, let's recreate Sakai-san's actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.63,0:15:31.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.58,0:15:34.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could you follow Sonoko-neechan's \Ninstructions?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.77,0:15:35.70,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.21,0:15:38.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one route Sakai-san, \Nwho was in the kitchen,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.27,0:15:42.11,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,could have taken to reach the \Ncrime scene in the bathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.11,0:15:43.21,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,without passing by the tables.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.21,0:15:43.71,Hallway,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,59)}Kitchen
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.67,0:15:45.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He exited through the kitchen window,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.46,0:15:48.69,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,crossed the yard, entered \Nthrough the front entrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.21,0:15:46.67,Hallway,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Hallway
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.69,0:15:50.93,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and reached the bathroom through the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.35,0:15:55.09,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He followed the same route \Nto return to the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.09,0:15:56.97,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That's the route you want \Nme to recreate, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.24,0:15:58.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.39,0:16:00.73,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.10,0:16:03.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay... Ready, go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.02,0:16:28.04,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,How was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.53,0:16:31.30,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's been 90 seconds so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.04,0:16:47.31,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Hup.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.97,0:16:48.82,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.13,0:16:51.60,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Two minutes, 50 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.56,0:17:01.66,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That sound we heard... \Nwas the timer in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.87,0:17:01.66,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What was that beeping sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.26,0:17:03.28,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.00,0:17:06.58,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,What does all of this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.81,0:17:09.96,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It means you don't have an alibi anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.28,0:17:10.91,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.64,0:17:16.72,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You said you were in the kitchen frying \Ndonuts when the crime took place,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.03,0:17:20.72,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,but you could have gone anywhere \Nduring the three minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.03,0:17:23.22,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,after you put the donuts in the fryer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.68,0:17:29.73,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But, why were Nonaka-san's \Ngloves in the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.33,0:17:34.83,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,If you assume Sakai-san set everything \Nup, doesn't that explain it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.45,0:17:41.56,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Your leading statements made me \Nsuspicious of you from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.56,0:17:43.12,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.47,0:17:47.29,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I understand that I could've gone to \Nthe bathroom and back in three minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.74,0:17:51.14,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't there a big hole in your reasoning?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.69,0:17:53.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.13,0:17:56.28,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Allow me to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.28,0:17:58.38,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.84,0:18:01.47,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.47,0:18:02.51,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,It's this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.96,0:18:07.14,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,While you were having tea in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.14,0:18:10.27,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,how did I cross this section of the yard?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.68,0:18:14.52,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,No one could pass through \Nhere without being seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.29,0:18:17.71,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.71,0:18:19.45,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.84,0:18:20.45,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.45,0:18:24.95,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're able to pass through \Nthis area without being seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.15,0:18:27.71,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.98,0:18:29.61,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I meant exactly what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.61,0:18:34.95,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You did in fact pass through this \Nyard and return to the kitchen
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.95,0:18:37.09,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,without being noticed by anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.34,0:18:39.33,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't even see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.33,0:18:41.56,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Show me the evidence, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.56,0:18:45.31,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the evidence has been standing \Nin front of us this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.31,0:18:46.10,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.10,0:18:47.98,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Look closely at the yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.20,0:18:51.90,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Look very closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.69,0:19:00.36,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently you took care of that yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.36,0:19:04.74,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Making it the same color as your uniform \Nmust've required a lot of patience.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.00,0:19:07.87,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He blends in completely with the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.87,0:19:10.09,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He's perfectly camouflaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.09,0:19:13.00,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I borrowed the uniform in the changing room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.70,0:19:16.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But even with the camouflage,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.35,0:19:20.08,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,wouldn't someone notice if \Nhe passed through the yard?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.08,0:19:22.26,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It takes only a moment to cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.67,0:19:25.44,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's one thing if you're staring at the yard,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.44,0:19:27.98,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,but since everyone was focused \Non their tea and donuts,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.98,0:19:29.90,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,it was unlikely that anyone would notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.50,0:19:32.06,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He probably even planned where
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.06,0:19:35.15,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and how he could cross the yard \Nunnoticed when he set it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.15,0:19:38.15,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,No. That's just speculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.47,0:19:40.40,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You need more proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.40,0:19:43.91,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's that scratch on your thigh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.16,0:19:50.63,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You got caught on the nail sticking out \Nof the wall on your way back, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.19,0:19:52.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.33,0:19:54.44,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.44,0:19:59.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Chiba said this cloth \Nwas stuck to a nail outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.40,0:20:01.42,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.78,0:20:05.43,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same color cloth \Nas Sakai-san's uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.86,0:20:08.08,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,If the police examine that cloth,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.08,0:20:11.43,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they'll find that \Nit came from your uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.89,0:20:14.87,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,There's even more evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.87,0:20:19.15,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently forensics reported that they \Nfound the laxatives you gave Nonaka-san
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.76,0:20:26.57,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,so he'd go to the bathroom \Nin the water on his table.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.82,0:20:30.58,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know it was me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.05,0:20:33.62,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,My plan was perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.62,0:20:34.98,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It was the donuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.98,0:20:36.08,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The donuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.43,0:20:40.18,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,This café's donuts are made to order.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.18,0:20:43.84,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You began frying new ones when \Nno new customers had entered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.30,0:20:47.60,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I considered what that might mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.06,0:20:53.35,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,It's all his fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.12,0:20:59.19,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I came up with the menu, the \Nconcept, and the eye-catching yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.64,0:21:02.59,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,But he kept me working part-time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.59,0:21:04.36,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't give me anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.08,0:21:06.70,DCMain,SAKAI,0000,0000,0000,,So I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.46,0:21:16.07,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently the manager's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.07,0:21:19.14,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I guess this case is closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.14,0:21:21.44,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You experienced your own share of misfortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.23,0:21:23.13,DCMain,NONAKA,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.40,0:21:25.66,DCMain,FURUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I should get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.66,0:21:27.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Furukawa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.75,0:21:30.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't paid yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.47,0:21:33.62,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.34,0:21:37.90,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Furukawa-san, you were \Ngoing to dine and dash?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.15,0:21:39.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.07,0:21:42.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Because Furukawa-san unconsciously \Ntouched his wallet in his back pocket
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.39,0:21:46.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,when Nonaka-san accused him,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.60,0:21:48.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko-neechan said it might be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.60,0:21:52.79,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Furukawa-san, could you \Ntell us more about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.06,0:21:55.91,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he was acting \Nnervous the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.91,0:21:57.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.58,0:22:00.46,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.32,0:23:26.92,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Solving that case made me hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.16,0:23:29.65,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.65,0:23:30.84,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.84,0:23:32.86,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,There's always room for sweets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.86,0:23:36.66,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,And after eating sweets, \Nyou need something salty.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.66,0:23:39.42,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. There's always room for more.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.83,0:23:43.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What about low sugar and \Nlow—well, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.58,0:23:47.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.25,0:23:48.50,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.50,0:23:50.70,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll blow her brains out!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.93,0:23:52.01,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.01,0:23:55.45,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,I expect you to fulfill the \Nthree demands I'm about to list.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.45,0:23:57.99,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,First, I want a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.99,0:24:00.25,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bring me a car so I can get out of—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.42,0:24:07.21,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.38,0:24:08.96,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Kyogoku Makoto the Understudy (Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.48,0:24:14.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is, "Kyogoku \NMakoto the Understudy, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.91,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Stunt
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.46,0:24:32.95,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.95,0:24:34.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Stunts!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:36.44,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Today's is the last episode of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:39.91,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.44,0:24:38.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Thank you for another year.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.12,0:24:39.71,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Happy New Year.
